Difference Pairs

We need to check whether there exists a pair (i, j) such that:

∣A[i]−A[j]∣=B
Efficient Idea (HashSet)
Store all array elements in a HashSet.
For every element x:
Check if x + B exists in the set.
Check if x - B exists in the set.
If either exists, a valid pair is found.
Otherwise, return 0.
Time Complexity
Building HashSet: O(N)
Checking each element: O(N)
Total: O(N)
Space Complexity
O(N) for the HashSet.
Java Solution
import java.util.HashSet;

public class Solution {

    public static int hasPairWithDifference(int[] A, int N, int B) {

        HashSet<Integer> set = new HashSet<>();

        // Store all elements in HashSet
        for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
            set.add(A[i]);
        }

        // Check for required difference
        for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
            if (set.contains(A[i] + B) || set.contains(A[i] - B)) {
                return 1;
            }
        }

        return 0;
    }
}
Example

Input

N = 6, B = 78
A = [5, 10, 3, 2, 50, 80]

Output

1

Explanation

|80 - 2| = 78, therefore a valid pair exists.
